  <cateringDescription><![CDATA[<p>Le Terril Blanc is offered on a half board basis.</p>
<p>Each morning a buffet breakfast is served between 7:30am - 10am in the hotel lounge area, overlooking the lake.</p>
<p>A two course dinner, with choice of starter and main course, <strong>or</strong> main course and dessert is available each day. This is served in a partner restaurant which is around 300m walk away.</p>]]></cateringDescription>
  <deactivateThisPage>0</deactivateThisPage>
  <description><![CDATA[<p><span>Having opened in 1967, the Leclerq family have welcomed numerous guests over the years and continue to provide a friendly welcome and comfortable accommodation. With just 24 bedrooms, you will be sure to have a personable welcome. </span>Hotel Le Terril Blanc has a great location in the centre of <a data-udi="umb://document/204ce8e4cf8c4ab09205501e16cb7565" href="/{localLink:umb://document/204ce8e4cf8c4ab09205501e16cb7565}" title="Tignes">Tignes</a> with amazing views of the frozen lake and mountains. </p>
<h2>Lake views</h2>
<p>With a great location near the centre of Tignes, the cosy Terril Blanc gives you access to the <a data-udi="umb://document/3f107aa9435442a892636b72e6e40b03" href="/{localLink:umb://document/3f107aa9435442a892636b72e6e40b03}" title="Tignes-Val d’Isere Ski Area">Tignes-Val d'Isere</a> ski area and even better views of the nearby lake and surrounding mountains. These views can be taken in by relaxing on the south facing terrace or with a drink in the bar and lounge area. </p>
<h2>Central location</h2>
<p>The ski lifts and slopes are just a snowballs throw away, warm your legs up on the gentles runs up from the Palafour chairlift, or head up <span>high-speed Tovière Gondola for quick access to the neighbouring resort of </span><a data-udi="umb://document/16c56b283bca4ae2b2ada820a5d3a03d" href="https://www.inghams.co.uk/ski-holidays/ski-resorts/france/tignes-val-d-isere-ski-area/val-disere" title="Val d'Isere">Val d’Isère.</a></p>
<p>If you are looking for a spot to have a bite to eat, there plenty of cafes and restaurants serving delicious Savoyard specialities, many with their own sun terrace - perfect for soaking up the winter sun. For a bit of after ski entertainment, choose between après ski in one of the local bars or head to the nearby Le Lagon for a dip in the pool and a well deserved rest in the sauna.</p>
<p> </p>
<p> </p>]]></description>
